== Amendments ==

## Old documents, now 06/20 meeting is including compromise amendments
## * [http://www.europarl.eu.int/meetdocs/2004_2009/organes/JURI/JURI_20050523_1500_audition.htm Offical translations of amendments for JURI] :
## ** Item entitled "3. AUDITION: Patentability of computer-implemented inventions" gives translations (in 19 languages) of Amendment 1-39
## ** Item entitled "3. AM Patentability of computer-implemented inventions" gives translations (in 14 languages) of Amendments 40-256
 * [http://www.europarl.eu.int/meetdocs/2004_2009/organes/JURI/JURI_20050620_1500.htm Offical translations of amendments for JURI] :
   * Item entitled "4 PR Software" gives translations (in 19 languages) of Amendments 1-39
   * Item entitled "4 AM Software" gives translations (in 19 languages) of Amendments 40-256
   * Item entitled "4 AMC Software" gives translations (/for now just in English and Polish, check out above URL for updates) of Compromise Amendments 1-17

 * Draft set of FFII amendments for the JURI/Rocard report:
   * All amendments in one big file:[http://www.ffii.org/~jmaebe/ep2r/juri050503/357620fi.doc Microsoft Word],  [http://www.ffii.org/~jmaebe/ep2r/juri050503/am_all_FFII_Rocard.pdf Acrobat PDF] (last update: 2005/05/02, 16:12)
